 predation risk. Interactions between some of these effects and body mass (whilst controlling for forearm length) indicate that individual variation in body size and/or state-dependent effects of energy reserves also partly determined the use of nightly torpor in these bats.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Fjelldal, Mari Aas", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wright, Jonathan", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Stawski, Clare", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/8861e91a853ab8ed7c4c60b75327dc32", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/d3e1db65be48f5399cd7c0a1f0a4c041ad1052ed43acfd325c082647522ddc2d", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/CAC539XB", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/CAC539XB", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/f30f1bc4f2a0c3bc803edebec5e45a19!/b281089-283653", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1", "pages": "129-142", "title": "Oecologia", "volume": "197"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/8861e91a853ab8ed7c4c60b75327dc32"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:CAC539XB"}, {"identifier": "10.1007/s00442-021-05022-6"}], "communities": [{"id": "batlit"}, {"id": "biosyslit"}], "